context: The school track and field sports will have 4 track projects? 100M, 200M, 400M and 800M.In the second class, three boys Jianguo, Xiaojie, Daniel and three girls Dandan, Xiaoying and Shuzhen participated.The sports will have two regulations? (1) Each project must be attended by men and women at the same time or not.(2) Each person can only participate in one project.
question: If Jianguo participated in 100M or 200M, Daniel participated in 400M, and Dandan participated in 800M, which of the following must be true?
choices: ["Xiaojie participated in 800M.", "Jianguo participated in 100M.", "Xiaoying participated in 200M.", "Shuzhen participated in 400M."]
elim_rationales: {"B": "Jianguo might be in 200M instead of 100M, so 100M isn’t guaranteed", "C": "Under mixed‐gender pairing, Xiaoying can never end up in 200M"}

context: Some people are not bad people, so some bad people are not people."
question: Which of the following reasoning has the same structure as the above reasoning?
choices: ["Some bargains are not good, so some bargains are good.", "Some bargains are not fakes, so some fakes are not bargains.", "All commodities are valuable, therefore, all valuable are commodities.", "Some inventors are self-taught, so some self-taught are inventors."]
elim_texts: {"A": "Some bargains are not good, so some bargains are good.", "C": "All commodities are valuable, therefore, all valuable are commodities."}
elim_rationales: {"A": "draws a positive conclusion about the same subject (Some A are B) rather than converting the negative proposition", "C": "converts a universal affirmative (All A are B → All B are A) instead of a particular negative conversion"}
kept_texts: {"B": "Some bargains are not fakes, so some fakes are not bargains.", "D": "Some inventors are self-taught, so some self-taught are inventors."}

context: Plant the same amount of cucumber seedlings in the two experimental greenhouses, apply magnesium salt in the first greenhouse but not add in the second.The first produced 10 kg of cucumber and the second produced 5 kg.Since nothing but water was applied to the greenhouse, the higher yield of the first greenhouse must be due to magnesium salts.
question: Which of the following, if true, weakens the argument most severely?
choices: ["There is a small amount of magnesium in the soil of the two experimental greenhouses.", "In the third experimental greenhouse, a high nitrogen fertilizer was applied but no magnesium salt was added, and 7 kg of cucumber was produced.", "Four different cucumber varieties were planted in both experimental greenhouses.", "The soil quality and sunshine in the two experimental greenhouses are different."]
elim_texts: {"A": "There is a small amount of magnesium in the soil of the two experimental greenhouses.", "C": "Four different cucumber varieties were planted in both experimental greenhouses."}
elim_rationales: {"A": "Background magnesium in both soils does not challenge that added magnesium raised yield", "C": "Both greenhouses had the same cucumber varieties, so variety differences cannot account for the yield gap"}
kept_texts: {"B": "In the third experimental greenhouse, a high nitrogen fertilizer was applied but no magnesium salt was added, and 7 kg of cucumber was produced.", "D": "The soil quality and sunshine in the two experimental greenhouses are different."}
